This task was described as an encounter with a robber. Participants were asked to imagine being a server at a bar. They were told that at the end of the night, they were on their way home with their tips from the night in hand (the offer) when they encountered a robber. Participants could choose to relinquish their money (passive) or try to fight the robber (active). If they handed over the money, they would be missing out on their potential reward. If they tried to fight the robber, they incurred the cost of fighting. If successful, they kept the offer minus the cost, but if unsuccessful, they missed out on the reward associated with the offer and incurred an additional loss amounting to the cost of fighting. On each trial, t, the offer (o) was sampled from the 20-element array presented in Eq. (1):1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
